topReviews.Name: Anupam Bhagat
topReviews.PositiveDesc: I like living in Andheri East as I find convenient metro and train journeys to university and work. Close to my residence I observe parks, restaurants, and massive malls. My family enjoys Nana Nani Park, and I feel secure. Though I adore it, parking issues and noise must be quickly addressed.

topReviews.Name: Pinal Kothari
topReviews.PositiveDesc: I often advise Andheri East, as I see excellent metro, train and bus access daily. Here I recount my experiences where kids get top schools, huge shopping centres, and easy airport access. This venue is top priority for me. I advise customers here that traffic congestion and parking issues need attention.

topReviews.Name: Abhirami Dandekar
topReviews.PositiveDesc: Presently I live in Andheri East. Here's connectivity I adore. Daily for my job, I take the Blue Line subway. For my family, life is wonderful because of my experiences with nearby hospitals and safety. My recommendations are for the ongoing road dust and the frequent heavy traffic congestion. Everything is extremely close.

topReviews.Name: Kriti Jayeswal
topReviews.PositiveDesc: Having a house in Andheri East makes me really glad. My journey to MIDC offices is really quick. For traffic avoidance, I would recommend the Metro. Seven Hills Hospital and Bombay Cambridge School are great. I enjoy hanging around The Local. Still, I can admit that the continual road excavation irritates me and my neighbours.

topReviews.Name: Prem Kapoor
topReviews.PositiveDesc: I suggest Andheri East without hesitation to my clients. I underline close respected institutions and SevenHills Hospital. I point to SEEPZ, airport offices, and MIDC. I clarify metro line one, WEH, and rail accessibility. I have to emphasise important needs including parking design, drainage improvements, and traffic management in this area.

topReviews.Name: Anand Verma
topReviews.PositiveDesc: Since life at work is simple here, I am ecstatic living in Andheri East. I like nice communities and nearby offices. I travel daily utilizing Andheri station's Metro Line One, buses, and WEH. SevenHills is someone I trust. I rent a workplace. Here, I think the rent is expensive. Traffic and drainage problems confront me.

topReviews.Name: Anushka
topReviews.PositiveDesc: I love this place. Andheri East is ideally suited for the Mumbai hustle as it gives the city its actual commercial pulse. All within minutes, the local train station. Metro Line 1, Western Express Highway and foreign airport make up an unbeatable transport network. For my job in the adjacent MIDC/SEEPZ region, which is rather vital. Opportunities abound in the neighbourhood good social infrastructure including excellent hospitals and schools means all I need is always nearby. Contributing to the impression of security are mostly well-lit and kept roads. The one thing that absolutely has to be fixed is the ongoing absence of planned parking spaces, which causes needlessly stressful vehicle ownership here.

topReviews.Name: Niti
topReviews.PositiveDesc: I suggest Andheri East to customers. Close to SEEPZ, it is a significant residential and commercial centre. Connectivity is great with Western Express Highway and airport. Constant metro initiatives, Line 7A to the airport among others, are fostering connections. Daily simplicity comes from major malls, hospitals, and excellent schools. High rental demand is kept by strong office demand from corporate campuses and SEZs. Standard rental yields range from three to four and a half percent. Though they vary by neighborhood, prices per square foot typically reach the mid twenty thousand. Modern amenities and resale prospects abound in new residential developments. One aspect to work on is better arranged low-cost housing. I Support It as a Savvy Purchase.

topReviews.Name: Luv
topReviews.PositiveDesc: I believe Andheri East is one of the best-connected neighbourhoods in Mumbai. The railway station is nearby from the place, while the Metro Line 1 is also accessible from here. The best part is that you get access to the Central, Western, and Harbour railway networks as well. I work in the SEEPZ, and it is easily accessible from here as well. The BKC is also well-connected to the place, where my spouse works. Andheri East is slightly more affordable than the western part of the neighbourhood, which I feel is a big plus point. Parking slots are rarely available in the locality, and this is a key issue that needs to be highlighted.

topReviews.Name: Vishal
topReviews.PositiveDesc: I personally find Andheri East to be the best-connected neighbourhood of Mumbai. Living here for so many years has been a great experience for my entire family. There are quite a few well-known residential societies here, while the people are so friendly and well-behaved. You have the JVLR, Western Express Highway, Andheri-Kurla Road, and even the Metro Line 1 and access to Line 7. Then there’s the Andheri railway station as well. You’ll find it so easy to access the airport, the MIDC, SEEPZ, and even the BKC. Social amenities are readily available as well. What’s not to like? The only issue here is waterlogging during the monsoons and the absence of adequate greenery in some stretches.

topReviews.Name: Raghav
topReviews.PositiveDesc: I start my day with client meetings in Andheri East and enjoy the vibe and ease of the area. SEEPZ, MIDC and various office parks make it a robust jobs centre and enhance rental demand. The connectivity is great with the Western Express Highway, JVLR, and Mumbai Metro interchanges. Recent metro additions and future lines planned hold out the promise of improved mobility and quicker city connectivity. There are quite a few new residential launches and branded developments, so customers have new-age amenities and options. Green oases are scarce, but civic parks and tree-lined avenues provide relief and shade. My recommendation is Andheri East for working professionals who want work-life balance and investment opportunities. Two areas for improvement are traffic congestion in heavy traffic and intermittent drainage and road maintenance.

topReviews.Name: Raviranjan
topReviews.PositiveDesc: What’s not to like? I have been staying here for many years now. Andheri East is a very nice locality, and my family is one of the earliest people to be here. We are now here for three generations, even though that’s hard to believe! I love the connectivity to the airport, which is a non-negotiable factor for someone like me. I can reach the airport in about 17-18 minutes from my home, no matter when I travel. So, that’s a big plus point, not to mention the easy access to the Versova Beach. I love driving down there (takes hardly 14-15 minutes) and watching the sunrise or sunset. In fact, it has been my favourite pastime for many years now. All other infra and amenities are at par with most premium Mumbai localities, and property prices have appreciated tremendously.

topReviews.Name: Jiya
topReviews.PositiveDesc: Coming to Andheri East was one of our smartest moves, mainly due to its unrivaled location close to the airport and its phenomenal commercial development with centers like MIDC and SEEPZ providing such abundant job opportunities. The connectivity is fantastic; with the Andheri Railway Station, Metro, and the Western Express Highway within reach, traveling throughout Mumbai is quite convenient, and we like it more because it is also more affordable than Andheri West. Social infrastructure is complete with good schools and hospitals, and the neat street makes it safe, even late at night. Nevertheless, we would really appreciate immediate action on the issue of insufficient parking space, a perennial headache for car owners here.

topReviews.Name: Kunal
topReviews.PositiveDesc: Living in Andheri East is a lively and well linked experience. I enjoy the convenient proximity to Andheri Railway Station, Metro, and Western Express Highway. The area has top class schools like Bombay Cambridge International and Podar International, along with hospitals like Seven Hills and Wockhardt in the vicinity. Shopping at Phoenix Marketcity or Infinity Mall, and eating out at neighborhood restaurants, is easy. Parks such as Nana Nani Park provide a green look to the locality. Traffic on Western Express Highway during rush hours and waterlogging in case of rains remain areas for improvement. As a whole, Andheri East is ideal for those who wish for a vibrant, convenient, and contemporary lifestyle in Mumbai.

topReviews.Name: Tushar
topReviews.PositiveDesc:
Positives:
Dwelling in Andheri East was indeed a fulfilling experience. The area is well-serviced through the Western Express Highway and the Andheri Railway Station, which made commutation easy. Being close to the international airport was a big plus, particularly for those traveling frequently. The area had a range of shopping malls, restaurants, and entertainment venues, which provided a lively life. The fact that there existed top-notch educational institutions and medical facilities further enhanced the attraction. Nevertheless, I think that there is scope for improvement in the upkeep of green spaces and the improvement of waste disposal systems to further improve the quality of life in the area.

_source.seoDescription:
Built by Starwing Developers Pvt Ltd, Starwing I Stay is one of the premium upcoming Residential establishments of Mumbai. This marvellous project consists of a single tower that has over 20 floors, giving an amazing view of Andheri East and its surrounding areas. Its modern layout and spacious apartments are tailored for the comfort of each prospective investor, having the size configurations of 1 to 1 BHK Studio From 185 to 445 Sq.Ft.

The project has a variety of world-class amenities with a large number of recreational activities and will improve the lifestyle of its residents. This includes an open-to-sky terrace garden, a fitness centre that spreads up to 2 levels,a mini-theatre, a cafeteria and a swimming pool. You don’t have to fret about any security-related concerns, as the security team helps manage a separate visitor log to prevent mishaps.

Starwing I Stay has seamless connectivity with other key areas of the town makes it a premium Residential project. It helps access the nearby commute centres and service zones with utmost ease. Some of these include the DN Nagar Metro Station, Western Express Highway, Lokhandwala Market and Fun Republic Mall.


Why Invest in Starwing I Stay?

  • Smart Investment Opportunity: As Starwing I Stay is currently New Launch, investors can secure premium apartments at competitive prices with flexible payment plans. They can earn a rental yield of approximately 3% per annum.
  • Excellent Connectivity: Starwing I Stay is ideal for modern living in Andheri East, Mumbai, helping you stay connected with the city’s major landmarks. These include malls like the Phoenix Market City, eateries like Global Fusion, transportation facilities like the Marol Naka Metro Station, and recreation centres like Juhu Beach.
  • Premium Amenities: Starwing I Stay offers diverse amenities, including a Games Room with video games and air hockey, a fitness centre for Zumba and CrossFit, and a Library for quiet reading. Kids enjoy a play area with an art corner, while extras like dance, karaoke, and martial arts ensure recreation for all ages.
  • Perfectly Planned Units: Starwing I Stay boasts a meticulously planned layout with a sky-touching 22-story tower featuring fully furnished studio apartments. Each space is designed for maximum comfort, offering modular kitchens, contemporary bathrooms, and smart storage solutions.
  • Innovation Integrated into Everyday Living: Starwing I Stay integrates technology into everyday life with features like video doorbells, wireless vacuum cleaners, and fibre-optic WiFi. A society security mobile app and voice-command home automation further streamline convenience for all society members.


What is the Address of the Project?

The address of Starwing I Stay is Andheri East, Mumbai, Maharashtra. The Starwing I Stay PIN Code is 400069.

description.manualDesc:
Starwing I Stay is a residential development. It is planned as a large, well-managed housing setup with multiple towers. The focus is on simple city living rather than luxury detailing.

The project is located in Andheri East. It is one of Mumbai’s well-known residential areas. The location provides easy access to daily travel routes and city roads. Markets, schools, hospitals, and work zones are nearby. Public transport options are also available nearby. 

Starwing I Stay spans over 3.5 acres of land. It offers 1 and 2-BHK homes. Apartment sizes range from 185 sq ft to 611 sq ft. There are 1,158 homes across the project. The project has clearly defined towers. Towers D, E, F, and G are planned for 1-bedroom homes. Studio homes are planned in Towers H, I, J, and K. This separation helps keep internal movement simple and structured.

Most homes come ready with basic fittings. Living rooms are air-conditioned for everyday comfort. Kitchens are modular and easy to use. Wall-mounted beds and wardrobes with loft storage are already provided. Alexa-based automation supports simple daily tasks.

The project functions as a gated residential community. Entry points and internal access are controlled. Common areas are designed to handle regular movement without crowding.

Starwing I Stay is developed by Starwing Developers Pvt Ltd. The group was founded in 1989. They have completed 22 residential and commercial projects. This development follows their experience with large-scale housing formats.

Amenities at Starwing I Stay, Andheri East, Mumbai

Lifestyle Spaces Designed for Everyday Living and Leisure

  • Four-level clubhouse spread across 12,000 sq ft for fitness, events, and social time.
  • Modern gymnasium, boxing ring, and fitness zones for strength, cardio, and group workouts.
  • Banquet hall, mini theatre, and karaoke room planned for celebrations and entertainment.
  • Coffee lounge, convenience store, cloud kitchen, ATM, and a doctor's clinic for daily needs.
  • Open-sky lounge spaces including sky cinema, rooftop party area, and open-air bar with BBQ.

Podium-Level Activity Zones

  • Multipurpose sports court with basketball and indoor game zones.
  • Gaming areas with video games, air hockey, foosball, a pool table, and board games.
  • Dedicated fitness and aerobic zones for Zumba and cross-fit sessions.
  • Library and e-library rooms for reading and quiet time.
  • Dance practice area, martial arts rooms, and brain game zones for skill building.

Sky-Level Leisure and Wellness Space 

  • A walking and jogging track is placed along open skyline views.
  • Sky gymnasium with herbal garden surroundings.
  • Yoga pavilion and meditation zones for calm daily routines.
  • Sunrise corner and stargazing area with telescope setup.
  • Sky bar loungebarbecueue area, and pergola seating for evening gatherings.
  • Hammock zones, chalk wall, and bonfire setup for relaxed social time.
  • Board game lawns with floor chess, ludo, and rooftop Snakes and Ladders.
  • Adda zone, party lawn, and senior citizen seating for community bonding.

Starwing I Stay, Andheri East, Mumbai: Perfectly Connected and Smartly Placed

Andheri East offers vibrant city life, seamless connectivity, modern comforts, and a thriving residential lifestyle.

Convenience:

  • Versova Metro Station- 0.1 km
  • Andheri Railway Station- 3.5 km
  • Western Express Highway- 4 km
  • Mumbai International Airport- 7.3 km

blogCMSContent.post_content:
Known for its good connectivity, diverse opportunities, and stellar infrastructure, Andheri East is a vibrant locality in the western part of Mumbai. The neighbourhood is a residential and commercial hub that attracts many young professionals and families. 

Andheri East boasts an abundance of quality infrastructure, excellent hospitals, schools, restaurants, and entertainment areas. Moreover, the real estate here is more affordable than the nearby localities, such as Andheri West, which makes it a desirable option for people looking to live in a well-connected and modern area without burning a hole in their pockets.

The neighbourhood is close to Andheri Railway Station, Andheri Metro Station, and Chhatrapati Shivaji Maharaj International Airport, which makes it easily accessible for both domestic and international visitors. 

The ample green spaces and affordable living spaces are among the top reasons Andheri East stands out from its neighbouring areas.  

What is Good in Andheri East?

  • Exceptional connectivity, both by road, metro, and air. 
  • A thriving commercial and business hub that offers numerous employment opportunities.
  • Presence of reputed educational institutions, including Bombay Cambridge International School, Podar International School, and Narayana E-Techno School.
  • Projects by many famous real estate developers, such as Lodha Group and Mahindra Lifespaces.
  • Availability of quality healthcare facilities, shopping malls, and parks.
  • Close to major employment hubs, including Bandra Kurla Complex and MIDC.
  • Well-lit, maintained, and clean streets. 

What Can Be Better in Andheri East?

  • Waterlogging due to heavy rainfall during monsoon.
  • Heavy traffic on the Western Express Highway during peak hours.
  • Insufficient parking space in the neighbourhood is a cause of concern for residents.
  • Air and noise pollution increases during peak hours.

Physical Infrastructure and Livability Index

Andheri East has a well-developed road, metro, and local train network. The nearest metro station is Andheri, located on the Blue Line of the Mumbai Metro, just 15 minutes away. The Blue Line connects the entire Andheri suburb. 

The Andheri Railway Station is about 3 kilometres from the neighbourhood, enabling residents to travel using trains. Moreover, the Chhatrapati Shivaji Maharaj International Airport is also located in close vicinity of the neighbourhood, approximately 15 minutes drive. 

Andheri East is also served by a well-connected network of roads. These include the Jogeshwari-Vikhroli Link Road, connecting Andheri with the eastern parts of Mumbai, and the Andheri-Kurla Road, connecting Eastern and Western Mumbai. The Western Express Highway is another major arterial road passing through Andheri East that provides access to various commercial and residential hubs.  

Social Infrastructure 

Andheri East’s social infrastructure caters to the needs of its residents and visitors well. The neighbourhood hosts well-established schools, hospitals, corporate offices, and entertainment institutions. Phoenix Marketcity and Infinity Mall are also located in close proximity to Andheri East and provide residents with the perfect opportunity for retail therapy and spending time with friends.

With several upscale restaurants, street food stalls, and local eateries, the neighbourhood also offers people the chance to indulge in diverse cuisines.

Popular Roads in Andheri East

Andheri East is well connected to its neighbouring localities because of the excellent road infrastructure. These roads also connect the neighbourhood to different parts of Mumbai. 

  • Andheri Kurla Road: This road connects Andheri East to Kurla, a neighbouring suburb. Being a crucial link between Eastern and Western Mumbai, the road often faces heavy traffic. 
  • Western Express Highway: This road connects the neighbourhood to different parts of Mumbai. It also facilitates access to various residential areas and commercial hubs surrounding Andheri East. 
  • Jogeshwari-Vikhroli Link Road: A well-developed road, the Jogeshwari-Vikhroli Link Road is a crucial link between Andheri East and other eastern suburbs of Mumbai.

Nearby Localities to Andheri East - Distance Calculator

Andheri East is located in a convenient location with many popular localities situated nearby. These include Andheri West, Powai, Vile Parle, and Goregaon East. The average distance and commuting times between Andheri East and different neighbourhoods are as follows:

Transport Services Available

There is plenty of public transportation available in Andheri East. This includes local trains, metro, taxis, and auto-rickshaws. You can travel to the neighbourhood from Andheri Railway Station, about 3 kilometres away, or Jogeshwari Railway Station, about 3.5 kilometres away. 

The area is also close to Andheri Metro Station (2.7 kilometres away), so it is convenient for people to travel using the metro. The airport is about 3 kilometres from the neighbourhood, and one can take an auto or cab to reach here.  

How People Rate Andheri East

The residents of Andheri East have provided positive ratings for the locality. They’ve appreciated the high standard of living and affordable pricing in the suburb. The neighbourhood is highly secure and offers all the basic amenities conveniently. Good schools, healthcare facilities, shopping malls, and entertainment areas are all located in the vicinity. 

In addition, Andheri East’s bustling markets and ample employment opportunities attract many people. The locality offers stellar connectivity to all prominent parts of Mumbai, well-maintained parks, and plenty of parking spaces. 

How to Visit Andheri East?

Travelling to Andheri East is easy due to plenty of public transportation and its well-planned layout. If you are travelling from another state or country, the Chhatrapati Shivaji Maharaj International Airport is located within close vicinity of the neighbourhood. 

You can also reach Andheri East by using local trains. The Andheri Railway Station is only 3 kilometres away, while the Jogeshwari Railway Station is also nearby. 

With Mumbai’s flourishing metro system, you can also reach the neighbourhood. The Andheri Metro Station on the Blue Line is just 2.7 kilometres away. 

Places to Visit in Andheri East

Andheri East has ample tourist places to delight visitors and residents. Located on the junction between Jogeshwari-Vikhroli Link Road and SEEPZ, the Mahakali Caves are ancient rock-cut caves and a popular tourist place in Mumbai. The place attracts history buffs and people interested in rich cultural and architectural heritage. 

Situated in the vicinity of Andheri East, Juhu Beach is another popular destination for locals and tourists alike. You can spend a relaxing day on the beach and enjoy a picnic day with loved ones. 

Jogeshwari Caves, also called Amboli Caves, is another top attraction of Andheri East. Being one of the earliest cave temples in India, it attracts many history enthusiasts, art lovers, and spiritual seekers. 

If you are looking for some retail therapy or shopping, the Infinity Mall in Andheri West won’t disappoint. The mall has a variety of retail outlets, gaming zones, eateries, and a cinema for the enjoyment of the visitors. 

Locality Comparison

Offering convenience, affordability, and amenities, Andheri East is a compelling choice for people seeking homes. The neighbourhood caters to people with different budgets. It offers a wide range of residential options, including apartments, housing societies, and gated communities.

It is also close to several quality educational institutions, hospitals, shopping complexes, and entertainment areas, which adds to its appeal. 

While Andheri West is similar to Andheri East in some areas, it is more expensive in terms of real estate. Andheri East, on the other hand, also offers better connectivity to Chhatrapati Shivaji Maharaj International Airport. 

Andheri East offers all the essential amenities to locals and more, multiple employment opportunities, and all means of transportation, including an airport, metro, local trains, and cabs. This makes the neighbourhood a popular option among home seekers.

developer.name: Lodha
developer.description:
The Lodha Group is one of the country’s foremost developers and is amongst the elite league of multinational real estate entities with a significant presence both in India and the United Kingdom. Lodha Developers is one of the most profitable companies in the Indian real estate sector and has built several landmark projects over the years.

Lodha Builders is currently developing a whopping 43 million sq. ft. of prime realty space with the biggest land reserves in the Mumbai Metropolitan Region. It has 28 ongoing projects spread across Hyderabad, Pune, Mumbai and London and is also expanding its presence in Bangalore. The Group has the biggest land bank spreading over more than 6, 200 acres with approximate saleable area of 553 million sq. ft.

Some of the landmark Lodha projects pertain to its Building a Better Life motto including the iconic World One, the tallest residential tower in the world and the Palava City which is the country’s first Greenfield smart city. The Group has brought some of the biggest global names/brands like Trump, Armani/Casa, Jade Jagger, Philippe Starck, Greg Norman, Kelly Hoppen and Pei Cobb Freed to India. The Group is also famous for recording the largest land deal in the country till date when it purchased a plot from the Mumbai Metropolitan Region Development Authority in the year 2010 for a staggering INR 4, 053 crore. The Group has also acquired other land parcels in Thane, the famous Washington House property on Altamount Road from the American Government and also the Mumbai Textile Mills land parcel.

The Group acquired the iconic MacDonald House at Grosvenor Square in the year 2013. The Group has also acquired other sites in London and is targeting the delivery of 1, 000 homes every year from 2017 onwards. The Group has offices in Dubai, London and Shanghai and is set to open offices in Singapore and the United States of America as well. The Group has more than 25, 000 workmen at its project sites along with more than 1800 engineers, 800 management professionals and 150 architects and designers. CASA by Lodha is the consumer luxury arm of the Group which offers residences for the middle income segment. The Group also introduced branded office spaces with offerings at almost every level including corporate hubs, large scale campuses and even boutique office for emerging businesses.

Why Lodha?

All Lodha properties come with clean titles and deeds and top class designs. All Lodha residential projects have clearly differentiated branding and marketing and the Group offers top notch customer and after sales service as well. The Group develops environmentally friendly projects that come with sky gardens, landscaping and other measures. The Group also offers housekeeping, valet and other services to customers going by its hospitality-like approach towards development.

The Group assigns relationship managers to each customer and has efficient and advanced systems and processes both for development and also for customer management and service. The Group also believes in honesty, integrity and transparency as key principles for a successful journey ahead.

Major Projects:

  • Palava City- luxurious air conditioned homes in India’s first greenfield smart city with jaw dropping amenities along the Kalyan-Shil Road
  • Trump Tower- A collaborative landmark between Trump and Lodha, this offers ultra premium branded 3 and 4 BHK apartments at the prime location of Worli
  • New Cuffe Parade- Another landmark project spreading over 23 acres with the largest clubhouses in the country and easy access to the BKC and South Bombay
  • Lodha Altamount- Ultra luxury at its best, these branded residences offer panoramic Arabian sea views, all glass facades, customization options and five star living on a 24-7 basis
  • Lodha Bellezza- South India’s tallest towers encompassing super luxurious 3 and 4 BHK sky villas along with other premium amenities near HITEC City

The Lodha Group is one of the country’s foremost developers and is amongst the elite league of multinational real estate entities with a significant presence both in India and the United Kingdom. Lodha Developers is one of the most profitable companies in the Indian real estate sector and has built several landmark projects over the years.

Lodha Builders is currently developing a whopping 43 million sq. ft. of prime realty space with the biggest land reserves in the Mumbai Metropolitan Region. It has 28 ongoing projects spread across Hyderabad, Pune, Mumbai and London and is also expanding its presence in Bangalore. The Group has the biggest land bank spreading over more than 6, 200 acres with approximate saleable area of 553 million sq. ft.

Some of the landmark Lodha projects pertain to its Building a Better Life motto including the iconic World One, the tallest residential tower in the world and the Palava City which is the country’s first Greenfield smart city. The Group has brought some of the biggest global names/brands like Trump, Armani/Casa, Jade Jagger, Philippe Starck, Greg Norman, Kelly Hoppen and Pei Cobb Freed to India. The Group is also famous for recording the largest land deal in the country till date when it purchased a plot from the Mumbai Metropolitan Region Development Authority in the year 2010 for a staggering INR 4, 053 crore. The Group has also acquired other land parcels in Thane, the famous Washington House property on Altamount Road from the American Government and also the Mumbai Textile Mills land parcel.

The Group acquired the iconic MacDonald House at Grosvenor Square in the year 2013. The Group has also acquired other sites in London and is targeting the delivery of 1, 000 homes every year from 2017 onwards. The Group has offices in Dubai, London and Shanghai and is set to open offices in Singapore and the United States of America as well. The Group has more than 25, 000 workmen at its project sites along with more than 1800 engineers, 800 management professionals and 150 architects and designers. CASA by Lodha is the consumer luxury arm of the Group which offers residences for the middle income segment. The Group also introduced branded office spaces with offerings at almost every level including corporate hubs, large scale campuses and even boutique office for emerging businesses.

Why Lodha?

All Lodha properties come with clean titles and deeds and top class designs. All Lodha residential projects have clearly differentiated branding and marketing and the Group offers top notch customer and after sales service as well. The Group develops environmentally friendly projects that come with sky gardens, landscaping and other measures. The Group also offers housekeeping, valet and other services to customers going by its hospitality-like approach towards development.

The Group assigns relationship managers to each customer and has efficient and advanced systems and processes both for development and also for customer management and service. The Group also believes in honesty, integrity and transparency as key principles for a successful journey ahead.

developer.name: Lodha
developer.description:
The Lodha Group is one of the country’s foremost developers and is amongst the elite league of multinational real estate entities with a significant presence both in India and the United Kingdom. Lodha Developers is one of the most profitable companies in the Indian real estate sector and has built several landmark projects over the years.

Lodha Builders is currently developing a whopping 43 million sq. ft. of prime realty space with the biggest land reserves in the Mumbai Metropolitan Region. It has 28 ongoing projects spread across Hyderabad, Pune, Mumbai and London and is also expanding its presence in Bangalore. The Group has the biggest land bank spreading over more than 6, 200 acres with approximate saleable area of 553 million sq. ft.

Some of the landmark Lodha projects pertain to its Building a Better Life motto including the iconic World One, the tallest residential tower in the world and the Palava City which is the country’s first Greenfield smart city. The Group has brought some of the biggest global names/brands like Trump, Armani/Casa, Jade Jagger, Philippe Starck, Greg Norman, Kelly Hoppen and Pei Cobb Freed to India. The Group is also famous for recording the largest land deal in the country till date when it purchased a plot from the Mumbai Metropolitan Region Development Authority in the year 2010 for a staggering INR 4, 053 crore. The Group has also acquired other land parcels in Thane, the famous Washington House property on Altamount Road from the American Government and also the Mumbai Textile Mills land parcel.

The Group acquired the iconic MacDonald House at Grosvenor Square in the year 2013. The Group has also acquired other sites in London and is targeting the delivery of 1, 000 homes every year from 2017 onwards. The Group has offices in Dubai, London and Shanghai and is set to open offices in Singapore and the United States of America as well. The Group has more than 25, 000 workmen at its project sites along with more than 1800 engineers, 800 management professionals and 150 architects and designers. CASA by Lodha is the consumer luxury arm of the Group which offers residences for the middle income segment. The Group also introduced branded office spaces with offerings at almost every level including corporate hubs, large scale campuses and even boutique office for emerging businesses.

Why Lodha?

All Lodha properties come with clean titles and deeds and top class designs. All Lodha residential projects have clearly differentiated branding and marketing and the Group offers top notch customer and after sales service as well. The Group develops environmentally friendly projects that come with sky gardens, landscaping and other measures. The Group also offers housekeeping, valet and other services to customers going by its hospitality-like approach towards development.

The Group assigns relationship managers to each customer and has efficient and advanced systems and processes both for development and also for customer management and service. The Group also believes in honesty, integrity and transparency as key principles for a successful journey ahead.

Major Projects:

  • Palava City- luxurious air conditioned homes in India’s first greenfield smart city with jaw dropping amenities along the Kalyan-Shil Road
  • Trump Tower- A collaborative landmark between Trump and Lodha, this offers ultra premium branded 3 and 4 BHK apartments at the prime location of Worli
  • New Cuffe Parade- Another landmark project spreading over 23 acres with the largest clubhouses in the country and easy access to the BKC and South Bombay
  • Lodha Altamount- Ultra luxury at its best, these branded residences offer panoramic Arabian sea views, all glass facades, customization options and five star living on a 24-7 basis
  • Lodha Bellezza- South India’s tallest towers encompassing super luxurious 3 and 4 BHK sky villas along with other premium amenities near HITEC City

images.description:
Welcome to Lodha Supremus Andheri, a commercial development located in Andheri East. This master plan, which also serves as the first-floor plan, showcases a single, meticulously designed commercial building featuring numerous office units. The plan details the building's layout and its immediate surroundings.

Land Use & Density

This property is designated for commercial office use, clearly indicated by the multiple 'OFFICE' units found on the first floor. Complementing these commercial spaces are essential facilities such as 'TOILET' areas, 'LIFT LOBBY' zones, and a central 'LOBBY.' The building is surrounded by green landscaping, which provides a pleasant open-space buffer. Additionally, a 'SUB-STATION' is strategically placed on the north-west side for utility provision. No specific density figures or land use percentages are outlined on this plan.

Connectivity & Access

developer.name: Lodha
developer.description:
The Lodha Group is one of the country’s foremost developers and is amongst the elite league of multinational real estate entities with a significant presence both in India and the United Kingdom. Lodha Developers is one of the most profitable companies in the Indian real estate sector and has built several landmark projects over the years.

Lodha Builders is currently developing a whopping 43 million sq. ft. of prime realty space with the biggest land reserves in the Mumbai Metropolitan Region. It has 28 ongoing projects spread across Hyderabad, Pune, Mumbai and London and is also expanding its presence in Bangalore. The Group has the biggest land bank spreading over more than 6, 200 acres with approximate saleable area of 553 million sq. ft.

Some of the landmark Lodha projects pertain to its Building a Better Life motto including the iconic World One, the tallest residential tower in the world and the Palava City which is the country’s first Greenfield smart city. The Group has brought some of the biggest global names/brands like Trump, Armani/Casa, Jade Jagger, Philippe Starck, Greg Norman, Kelly Hoppen and Pei Cobb Freed to India. The Group is also famous for recording the largest land deal in the country till date when it purchased a plot from the Mumbai Metropolitan Region Development Authority in the year 2010 for a staggering INR 4, 053 crore. The Group has also acquired other land parcels in Thane, the famous Washington House property on Altamount Road from the American Government and also the Mumbai Textile Mills land parcel.

The Group acquired the iconic MacDonald House at Grosvenor Square in the year 2013. The Group has also acquired other sites in London and is targeting the delivery of 1, 000 homes every year from 2017 onwards. The Group has offices in Dubai, London and Shanghai and is set to open offices in Singapore and the United States of America as well. The Group has more than 25, 000 workmen at its project sites along with more than 1800 engineers, 800 management professionals and 150 architects and designers. CASA by Lodha is the consumer luxury arm of the Group which offers residences for the middle income segment. The Group also introduced branded office spaces with offerings at almost every level including corporate hubs, large scale campuses and even boutique office for emerging businesses.

Why Lodha?

All Lodha properties come with clean titles and deeds and top class designs. All Lodha residential projects have clearly differentiated branding and marketing and the Group offers top notch customer and after sales service as well. The Group develops environmentally friendly projects that come with sky gardens, landscaping and other measures. The Group also offers housekeeping, valet and other services to customers going by its hospitality-like approach towards development.

The Group assigns relationship managers to each customer and has efficient and advanced systems and processes both for development and also for customer management and service. The Group also believes in honesty, integrity and transparency as key principles for a successful journey ahead.

Major Projects:

  • Palava City- luxurious air conditioned homes in India’s first greenfield smart city with jaw dropping amenities along the Kalyan-Shil Road
  • Trump Tower- A collaborative landmark between Trump and Lodha, this offers ultra premium branded 3 and 4 BHK apartments at the prime location of Worli
  • New Cuffe Parade- Another landmark project spreading over 23 acres with the largest clubhouses in the country and easy access to the BKC and South Bombay
  • Lodha Altamount- Ultra luxury at its best, these branded residences offer panoramic Arabian sea views, all glass facades, customization options and five star living on a 24-7 basis
  • Lodha Bellezza- South India’s tallest towers encompassing super luxurious 3 and 4 BHK sky villas along with other premium amenities near HITEC City

images.description:
The project, named Lodha Supernova, features 11 distinct buildings or towers within its master plan. Details regarding the total land area, number of units, project launch, and completion dates are not visible in the provided master plan.

Land Use & Density

The master plan for Lodha Supernova primarily features residential blocks, indicated by the numbered buildings, integrated with extensive green and recreational spaces. There's a designated area for 'FUTURE DEVELOPMENT' on the western side of the site. The layout emphasizes open areas such as various lawns, decks, and water bodies, providing ample communal spaces alongside the residential structures.

Connectivity & Access
  • The property incorporates multiple 'DROP-OFF LOBBY' (31) points, providing direct access to the individual residential buildings.
  • Internal pathways are designed to connect the various buildings and amenity zones throughout the site.
  • External connectivity includes Mathuradas Vasanji Road (0.6 km), Krantiveer Lakhuji Salve Marg (1.3 km), Western Express Highway (2.2 km), and Mahakali Caves Road (1.1 km).
On-Site Features & Amenities
  • Residents have access to a comprehensive aquatic area, featuring a 25M Lap Pool, a Kid's Pool, a Jacuzzi Lounge, and unique water features like a Shallow Pool with Glass Water Cube and Water Cascades.
  • Leisure and social spaces include a dedicated Club House (32), various themed lawns such as a Function Lawn, Sports Lawn, Party Lawn, and Yoga Lawn, and specialized decks like the Meditation Deck and Family Deck.
  • The master plan also includes specific recreational zones like a Chill-Out Court, a Multipurpose Hard Court, a Kid's Play Area, and unique elements like a Ganesh Temple.
Key Dimensions & Figures
  • The main 25M Lap Pool (21) has a depth of 1.2 meters.
  • The Kid's Pool (17) is designed with a depth of 0.5 meters, suitable for younger residents.
  • The Jacuzzi Lounge (22) features a depth of 0.9 meters.
  • A unique Water Rill with Bubblers (9) is present, with a shallow depth of 0.1 meters.

developer.name: Kalpataru
developer.description:
The Kalpataru Group is one of Mumbai’s leading developers and has been a key player in the industry for over four decades. Kalpataru Developers is known for pioneering innovations, superior project execution and awe inspiring designs. Kalpataru Builders has definitely played its part in transforming the Mumbai skyline with several landmark projects till date. Founded in 1969 by Mofatraj P. Munot, the Group has won several laurels and awards for its projects.

The portfolio of Kalpataru properties encompasses high end commercial, residential and retail projects in addition to lifestyle gated communities, integrated townships and redevelopment projects spreading across the Mumbai Metropolitan Region and Pune. The Group also has a significant presence in other markets like Surat, Hyderabad, Jaipur and Chennai. Apart from real estate, the Group also has interests in project management, engineering, procurement and construction (EPC), infrastructure projects, logistics, warehousing, roads, power transmission projects and property management solutions.

The Group was one of the biggest civil contracting firms working in the Middle East between 1974-1982 and is behind some of the biggest projects in the Gulf. There are more than 80 Kalpataru projects till date which have become landmarks in their own rights.

Why Kalpataru?

All Kalpataru residential projects are built with an eye on quality, innovation and customer centricity. The Group believes in values like humility, respect, prudence, business ethics, integrity, reliability, trust, transparency, customer commitment and long term relationships with customers and all stakeholders. Along with adhering to stringent quality standards, the Group also follows an Integrated Design Approach (IDeA).

This approach takes into account environmental impact, quality of life, cost, productivity, creativity, lifestyle benefits and future flexibility while creating project designs. The Group believes in sustainable, cost effective, productive, safe, functional and accessible development.

Major Projects:

  • Kalpataru Square- Located at Andheri, this the first project in Asia and the sixth project in the world to receive the US Green Building Council’s Platinum Level Certification LEED- Core & Shell
  • Kalpataru Horizon- Located at the prime South Mumbai location of Worli, this project has the first residential floor starting from the 14th floor to ensure that every apartment has gorgeous sea views
  • Kalpataru Habitat- Located at Parel, this is the first project in Mumbai to get an independent car park building along with other sporting facilities such as a golf putting green, tennis court and basketball court on top of the residential building

images.description:
Rustomjee Central Park Commercial. The project is located in Andheri East, with proximity to Andheri Kurla Road (0.1 km), Western Express Highway (0.5 km), and Mahakali Caves Road (0.2 km). The master plan depicts two main structures, A Wing and B Wing, along with ground floor commercial and amenity spaces.

This master plan for Rustomjee Central Park Commercial includes two main structures, A Wing and B Wing, and designates areas for retail, amenities, and parking. While total land area is not specified, the plan outlines the ground floor layout and carpet areas for commercial units within the B Wing.

Land Use & Density

The ground floor of B Wing features a dedicated 'RETAIL/EATING HOUSE' space, indicating a commercial use. There is also a 'BUILT-UP AMENITY SPACE' and a 'MAIN ENT. LOBBY' for B Wing. The site includes extensive landscaped areas with trees and planting, and dedicated surface and basement parking facilities.

Connectivity & Access
  • The property features a 'DOUBLE HEIGHT DRIVEWAY' for vehicular movement.
  • Primary access is facilitated through 'GATE 3', which serves as both an entry and exit point.
  • A dedicated 'MAIN ENT. LOBBY' provides access to B Wing.
  • Ramps are provided for 'RAMP DOWN TO BASEMENT' parking access.
On-Site Features & Amenities
  • A 'SECURITY CABIN' is positioned near the main entry/exit point for controlled access.
  • Utility services include a 'SUB STATION,' 'METER ROOM,' and a 'DG SET' for power backup.
  • The B Wing includes multiple 'LIFT' facilities and a 'MAIN ENT. LOBBY' for convenience.
  • There is a specified 'BUILT-UP AMENITY SPACE' and a 'MARKET OFFICE' on the ground floor.
Key Dimensions & Figures
  • The 'RETAIL/EATING HOUSE' on the ground floor of B Wing has a carpet area of 115.77 SQMT (1246.15 SQ.FT).
  • The dimensions for the 'RETAIL/EATING HOUSE' are provided as (15.24 + 14.202 X 8.18).
  • Minor variations of 0 +/- 3% in actual carpet areas may occur due to finishing tolerances and column projections.
  • The RERA carpet area mentioned in the plan includes usable carpet area for Balcony/Deck, as it is counted in F.S.I.

developer.name: Rustomjee
developer.description:
Rustomjee Developers is a leading real estate company and has developed several landmark projects over the years. Rustomjee Builders is synonymous with high quality materials, pioneering designs and architectural grandeur. The company has contributed towards transforming the skyline of Mumbai and its suburbs with its projects.

The portfolio of Rustomjee properties encompasses a whopping 10 million sq. ft. across corporate parks, luxury townships, retail spaces and more than 8, 500 housing units. The tally of Rustomjee projects built over the last five years cover 8 million sq. ft. and these are majorly concentrated in the Mumbai Metropolitan Region. Rustomjee Realty is focused on adding another 13 million sq. ft. to its kitty over the next five years.

Why Rustomjee?

All Rustomjee residential projects come with amenities like swimming pools and playgrounds along with other premium amenities. The company is child centric in terms of its planning and also builds eco friendly structures. The company follows an age old design philosophy where form follows function.

This aspect comes through in every design and layout. The company adheres to stringent quality standards for its projects as part of its Better, not cheaper philosophy. The company believes in customer centricity as a key attribute towards success and has innumerable happy customers under its belt. The company does not substitute price at the cost of quality. The company believes in a philosophy of teamwork with its customers. 100% customer satisfaction is a major objective at the company along with long term customer relationships.

The company is firmly committed towards delivering projects on time to customers along with innovation, design excellence, transparent processes and contemporary works systems in addition to superior quality and total accountability and transparency in all business dealings. The company offers amenities that cater to senior citizens, children and adults alike and all its projects also come with cutting edge security and safety measures. The company believes in living spaces as natural extensions of their environments. The company integrates futuristic technologies into its projects and fuses the same with classic and traditional design sensibilities while keeping 21st century lifestyle needs at the forefront at all times.

Major Projects

There are several landmark projects developed by the company over the years and the list also includes several Rustomjee upcoming projects. Here’s taking a look at some of them:

  • Rustomjee Paramount- This landmark project spreads over 1.65 acres at Khar West and offers a signature high rise that offers gorgeous views of the city and Arabian sea alike. The project offers unmatched luxury and wonderfully designed 1, 2, 3 and 4 BHK apartments. The project has been designed by renowned architects Sanjay Puri and Patty Mak and offers premium amenities and lavish lifestyles to residents
  • Rustomjee Season- This premium residential project is located at the BKC Annexe and come with bespoke residences designed by leading architect Sanjay Puri. The project spreads over 4 acres and offers premium amenities and facilities to residents along with luxuriously designed 3, 3.5 and 4 BHK apartments. Ambience is the major winner at this project
  • Rustomjee Meridian- This project is located at Kandivali and offers premium amenities and facilities to residents. The project encompasses a stunning 20 storied building which lies just three and a half kilometres away from the Kandivali station and offers great connectivity to the Link Road and SV Road. The Metro line is also easily accessible from the project

topProjects.FloorPlan:
The development features some of the most premium office spaces in a signature Rustomjee style in one of the most coveted office space neighbourhoods across Andheri. The spaces sprawl across an area of 1 Lac sq. ft. with two levels of basement and a 9-floor high multi-storey building. The tower is easily accessible with high-speed elevators, five in number and four staircases. 

The development also has two levels of parking and advanced flat slab technology that makes the areas as spacious as possible. Strategically well-thought-out and convenient, the project also features a grand entrance driveway and beautiful lobby and reception spaces. Detailed floor plan configurations can be accessed through the Rustomjee Central Park Brochure.

  • The Chhatrapati Shivaji Maharaj International Airport (4.3 km) is a short 15-minute drive from the project.

  • Educational Institutions like the Little Flower School are just 2.5 kilometres from the project. Other nearby schools are Marol Municipal High (3.1 km) and Sacred Heart School (3.9 km).

images.name: Master Plan Image 11
images.description:
Here's an overview of the Rustomjee Elements master plan. This plan features multiple residential wings surrounding a large central amenity area, designed to offer a connected living experience.

The Rustomjee Elements project consists of several residential wings, including AER (Wing G), AQUA (Wing F), ESPACE (Wing E), TERRA (Wing A), LUMIERE (Wing D), RENDEZVOUS (Wing B), and IGNIS (Wing C), which is also referred to as Wing SC. While the total number of units and land area aren't specified, the layout indicates a significant development with multiple towers.

Land Use & Density

The master plan allocates land primarily for residential towers and a substantial central green space dedicated to amenities and recreation. The buildings are arranged around this core, maximizing access to open areas. Specific percentages or units per acre are not detailed on the plan.

Connectivity & Access
  • The development is bordered by a 30.50 M. Wide Road on one side and a 9.15 M. Wide Road on another.
  • Internal pathways and roads connect all the residential wings and amenities within the complex.
  • There are clearly marked entry and exit points for vehicles and pedestrians, with an entry near Wing G and an exit near the Temple and Wing C.
On-Site Features & Amenities
  • A large, centrally located landscaped garden serves as a focal point, featuring recreational areas.
  • Dedicated play areas for children are integrated within the central green space.
  • A sports court is visible, providing facilities for various outdoor activities.
  • The plan includes a Temple, strategically placed near the exit point of the complex.
Key Dimensions & Figures
  • The project features two adjacent roads with widths of 30.50 meters and 9.15 meters.
  • The development is comprised of multiple distinct wings, named AER (G), AQUA (F), ESPACE (E), TERRA (A), LUMIERE (D), RENDEZVOUS (B), and IGNIS (C/SC).
  • Project registration details include P51800001362 for Wing SC (also known as Wing C/IGNIS) and P51800001736 for Wing E (ESPACE).

developer.description:
Mahindra Lifespaces Developers is known for offering premium and urban landscapes along with sustainable communities. Mahindra Lifespaces Builders is the first developer of green homes in the country. This philosophy of healthy living and green design influences all Mahindra Lifespaces residential projects.

Almost all Mahindra Lifespaces projects are pre-certified as Platinum rated green homes. The company is one of the first to receive this certification from the IGBC. The company has a pan-Indian presence and shot further into the limelight by developing the first integrated business city named Mahindra World City. The company is a part of the Mahindra Group, one of India’s most reputed and biggest business houses.

The portfolio of Mahindra Lifespaces properties encompasses more than 12.94 million sq. ft. across completed projects while upcoming and ongoing projects collectively cover around 9.44 million sq. ft. Mahindra World City developments in Jaipur and Chennai have firmly entrenched the company as a major force to reckon with in the national real estate scene. There are more than 125 Indian and global companies housed at these pioneering mixed use projects. The company has a significant presence in Mumbai, Delhi-NCR, Nagpur, Pune, Chennai, Hyderabad and Bangalore. The company aims at offering high quality housing at really affordable prices to customers through its brand called Happinest.

Why Mahindra Lifespaces?

The company offers housing solutions for almost every budget and also at really competitive and affordable prices in particular areas. The company aims at offering the highest possible returns from its projects to customers in all possible ways. The company emphasizes hugely on environment friendly project development. The company is known for its multidimensional and futuristic vision.

The company believes in green and healthy living solutions and believes in sustainable development above all else. The company also believes in core values like reliability, transparency and trust. The company plans and designs projects in accordance to customer needs in specific locations. The company offers mostly Platinum rated (IGBC) homes to residents. Other core values of the company include good corporate practices, business ethics, sustainability, professionalism, customer centricity and quality. The company emphasizes hugely on customer satisfaction above all else and adheres to stringent quality standards for its projects as well.

Major Projects

There are several landmark projects developed by the company and the list also includes some awe inspiring Mahindra Lifespaces upcoming projects as well. A few of these projects are given below:

  • Sylvan County- This premium residential project has been designed by Hafeez Contractor and is the first premium residential community in the Mahindra World City. The project spreads over 22 acres and comprises of 211 units in all. The project offers semi-detached homes, independent bungalows and beautifully landscaped apartments along with huge open spaces, ample natural light, fresh air and natural greenery. There are several premium amenities and facilities offered to residents at this project
  • Iris County- This premium project is a part of the Mahindra World City at Chennai. The project offers well designed homes amidst lush natural greenery and open spaces. The project offers multiple premium amenities and facilities to residents as well
  • Nova- This landmark project offers 1.5 and 2.5 BHK homes to residents at competitive prices in Mahindra World City at Chennai. The project offers access to retail and business zones along with every amenity and feature that you can think of

Mahindra Lifespaces Vivante, located in Andheri East, features a master plan organized into two distinct plots, one main area and an additional section designated as PLOT B. The plan shows a total of at least 10 towers, with Towers A1 through A6 in the primary area and Towers B1 through B4 in PLOT B. Specific total land area or unit counts are not provided in this master plan.
Land Use & Density The master plan allocates land for residential towers across two plots. Both plots integrate car park towers and a variety of recreational amenities. No commercial zones are indicated in the provided layout.
Connectivity & Access
  • The main entry and exit point for the primary plot is located on Suren Road.
  • A Proposed DP Road borders PLOT B and separates it from the main plot, also providing access to PLOT B.
  • Internal driveways are present throughout both sections of the development for circulation.
  • The property is approximately 0.4 km from the Western Express Highway, 1.2 km from Swami Vivekanand Road, and 2.8 km from Adi Shankaracharya Marg.
On-Site Features & Amenities
  • Residents have access to a Gym, an AV Room, and a Multipurpose Hall which includes Table Tennis facilities.
  • Recreational spaces include a Pool Table & Lounge, a Games Room & Creche, and a Kids Play Area.
  • Outdoor activities are supported by a Jogging Track, an Open Gym, a Basketball Hoop, and a Multipurpose Lawn.
  • Other amenities include an Open Chess Area and a Steam Room.
Key Dimensions & Figures
  • The development comprises at least 10 residential towers across its two plots.
  • A total of 14 distinct amenities are explicitly listed within the master plan.
  • Dedicated Car Park Towers are provided within both the main plot and PLOT B.

developer.name: Mahindra Lifespaces
developer.description:
Mahindra Lifespaces Developers is known for offering premium and urban landscapes along with sustainable communities. Mahindra Lifespaces Builders is the first developer of green homes in the country. This philosophy of healthy living and green design influences all Mahindra Lifespaces residential projects.

Almost all Mahindra Lifespaces projects are pre-certified as Platinum rated green homes. The company is one of the first to receive this certification from the IGBC. The company has a pan-Indian presence and shot further into the limelight by developing the first integrated business city named Mahindra World City. The company is a part of the Mahindra Group, one of India’s most reputed and biggest business houses.

The portfolio of Mahindra Lifespaces properties encompasses more than 12.94 million sq. ft. across completed projects while upcoming and ongoing projects collectively cover around 9.44 million sq. ft. Mahindra World City developments in Jaipur and Chennai have firmly entrenched the company as a major force to reckon with in the national real estate scene. There are more than 125 Indian and global companies housed at these pioneering mixed use projects. The company has a significant presence in Mumbai, Delhi-NCR, Nagpur, Pune, Chennai, Hyderabad and Bangalore. The company aims at offering high quality housing at really affordable prices to customers through its brand called Happinest.

Why Mahindra Lifespaces?

The company offers housing solutions for almost every budget and also at really competitive and affordable prices in particular areas. The company aims at offering the highest possible returns from its projects to customers in all possible ways. The company emphasizes hugely on environment friendly project development. The company is known for its multidimensional and futuristic vision.

The company believes in green and healthy living solutions and believes in sustainable development above all else. The company also believes in core values like reliability, transparency and trust. The company plans and designs projects in accordance to customer needs in specific locations. The company offers mostly Platinum rated (IGBC) homes to residents. Other core values of the company include good corporate practices, business ethics, sustainability, professionalism, customer centricity and quality. The company emphasizes hugely on customer satisfaction above all else and adheres to stringent quality standards for its projects as well.

Major Projects

There are several landmark projects developed by the company and the list also includes some awe inspiring Mahindra Lifespaces upcoming projects as well. A few of these projects are given below:

  • Sylvan County- This premium residential project has been designed by Hafeez Contractor and is the first premium residential community in the Mahindra World City. The project spreads over 22 acres and comprises of 211 units in all. The project offers semi-detached homes, independent bungalows and beautifully landscaped apartments along with huge open spaces, ample natural light, fresh air and natural greenery. There are several premium amenities and facilities offered to residents at this project
  • Iris County- This premium project is a part of the Mahindra World City at Chennai. The project offers well designed homes amidst lush natural greenery and open spaces. The project offers multiple premium amenities and facilities to residents as well
  • Nova- This landmark project offers 1.5 and 2.5 BHK homes to residents at competitive prices in Mahindra World City at Chennai. The project offers access to retail and business zones along with every amenity and feature that you can think of

images.name: Master Plan Image 5
images.description:
Vicino by Mahindra Lifespaces is a development spanning 6,717.78 square meters, offering 1 and 2 BHK Premium Homes. The master plan illustrates four residential towers, A1, A2, A3, and A4, alongside a 'Proposed Development' and an 'Automated Car Park Tower'. Common areas and amenities will be available upon the completion of the entire project.

Land Use & Density

The development dedicates space to residential towers and includes significant areas for proposed future development and an automated car park. Open spaces are integrated throughout the plan, featuring a Multipurpose Lawn, Nature Trail, and various recreational zones. Specific unit density or percentage allocations for different zones are not provided.

Connectivity & Access
  • The property features a main 'Entry & Exit' point and a 'Security Gate' located on Suren Road.
  • An internal road network connects the residential towers, automated car park, and amenity areas.
  • The development borders Suren Road and a 'Proposed Of Road' for external connectivity.
On-Site Features & Amenities
  • A Rooftop Swimming Pool offers a unique recreational space.
  • Fitness facilities include both an Open Gym and an Indoor Gym.
  • Leisure options comprise a Spa and an Indoor Games Room.
  • Outdoor activities are supported by a Kids' Play Area, Basketball Hoop, Reflexology Path, and a Multipurpose Lawn.
Key Dimensions & Figures
  • The total project area is 6,717.78 square meters.
  • The development focuses on 1 and 2 BHK Premium Homes.
  • The plan details 4 existing residential towers and an additional Automated Car Park Tower.
  • A total of 18 distinct amenities and features are listed within the master plan.

The company has a pan-Indian presence and shot further into the limelight by developing the first integrated business city named Mahindra World City. The company is a part of the Mahindra Group, one of India’s most reputed and biggest business houses.

The portfolio of Mahindra Lifespaces properties encompasses more than 12.94 million sq. ft. across completed projects while upcoming and ongoing projects collectively cover around 9.44 million sq. ft. Mahindra World City developments in Jaipur and Chennai have firmly entrenched the company as a major force to reckon with in the national real estate scene. There are more than 125 Indian and global companies housed at these pioneering mixed use projects. The company has a significant presence in Mumbai, Delhi-NCR, Nagpur, Pune, Chennai, Hyderabad and Bangalore. The company aims at offering high quality housing at really affordable prices to customers through its brand called Happinest.

The company aims at offering the highest possible returns from its projects to customers in all possible ways. The company emphasizes hugely on environment friendly project development. images.name: Master Plan Image 1
images.description:
Mahindra Vivante features 10 residential towers and is located in Andheri East. The project is accessible via Suren Road and a Proposed Off Road, with external connectivity to Swami Vivekanand Road (1.2 km), Western Express Highway (0.4 km), and Adi Sankaracharya Marg (2.8 km).

Land Use & Density

The master plan shows residential towers (A1-A6 and B1-B4) spread across the property, interspersed with various open recreational spaces and designated car park areas.

Connectivity & Access
  • The main access point, labeled 'Entry & Exit,' is situated on Suren Road.
  • Internal 'Drive Ways' are established to facilitate movement between the tower clusters and amenity areas.
  • The property benefits from frontage on Suren Road and also connects to a 'Proposed Off Road' on the eastern side.
  • External connectivity is provided through its proximity to Swami Vivekanand Road, Western Express Highway, and Adi Sankaracharya Marg.
On-Site Features & Amenities
  • A dedicated fitness and wellness block includes a Gym, Open Gym, and Steam Room.
  • Recreational facilities consist of an AV Room, Multipurpose Hall with Table Tennis, Pool Table & Lounge, Games Room & Creche, Basketball Hoop, and Open Chess Area.
  • Outdoor amenities such as a Kids Play Area, Jogging Track, and a Multipurpose Lawn are provided for varied activities.
Key Dimensions & Figures
  • The development incorporates 10 residential towers, identified as A1 through A6, and B1 through B4.
  • There are 14 distinct amenities and facilities explicitly labeled within the master plan.
  • The property has direct access from Suren Road and is also adjacent to a Proposed Off Road.
  • Multiple Car Park zones are allocated throughout the property's layout.

developer.description:
Oberoi Realty is one of the country’s biggest and most reputed developers. The company is always on a quest to ensure vibrant and fulfilling relationships between spaces and their occupants. The company began its journey almost three decades earlier with a view towards redefining housing solutions for customers at par with the best global parameters when the paradigm shift in Mumbai from the southern island towards the suburbs took place.

The portfolio of Oberoi Realty properties encompasses more than 39 projects at strategic locations in Mumbai which cumulatively comprise approximately 9.18 million sq. ft. The company is presently developing another 20.61 million sq. ft. in various parts of Mumbai and other regions. The company has always adhered to high quality design parameters for its projects and several of them have contributed immensely towards transforming the Mumbai skyline.

Why Oberoi Realty?

The company is known for its insistence on innovation and contemporary architecture in addition to top class project execution and quality construction. The company partners with the best in the country and the world and has always stayed abreast of evolving national and global trends in the industry. The company outsources work to leading global and domestic consultants in architecture, engineering, design and construction to accomplish the scalability required for undertaking mega projects.

The company makes use of the latest technologies for project development and believes in core values like transparency, trust and reliability. The company delivers projects on time and strives to create living spaces that enhance quality of life overall. The company is committed towards offering futuristic and revolutionary offerings which are ahead of their time and benchmarked against global practices and trends. The company aims at offering the perfect solutions to discerning customers and follows top class quality systems and processes. Customer centricity is taken very seriously at the company along with teamwork, innovation, honesty, accountability and its I Connect philosophy where open and transparent communication amongst stakeholders and customers is encouraged.

Major Projects

There are several landmark Oberoi Realty projects built over the years and here’s taking a look at some of them:

  • Priviera- This ultra luxurious and landmark project offers boutique privileges and comfort at one of the poshest residential locations in Mumbai. The project has been designed by the renowned Guz Architects form Singapore and the structural design has been taken care of by Meinhardt, an award winning firm from Singapore. The project is located in close proximity to the Arabian Sea and the domestic and international airports. The project comes with a rooftop infinity pool, gorgeous views of the Arabian Sea, a complete floor dedicated to every apartment, multiple parking levels and car lifts, 360 degree air and light ventilation and a show flat designed by Sussanne Khan and her Charcoal Project
  • Prisma- This landmark project offers spacious and beautifully designed 4 BHK apartments with spacious balconies to residents. The project comes with impeccable landscaping and lies along the Jogeshwari-Vikhroli Link Road. The project offers easy access to the Western Express Highway and offers premium amenities and facilities to residents
  • Oberoi Woods- This premium residential project is located at Goregaon East off the Western Express Highway and spreads over 80 acres in all. The project offers nature friendly layouts to residents along with gorgeous views of the Aarey greens. The project is characteristic of exquisite finishing, the very best and innovative construction techniques and contemporary designs and layouts

The company began its journey almost three decades earlier with a view towards redefining housing solutions for customers at par with the best global parameters when the paradigm shift in Mumbai from the southern island towards the suburbs took place.

The portfolio of Oberoi Realty properties encompasses more than 39 projects at strategic locations in Mumbai which cumulatively comprise approximately 9.18 million sq. ft. The company is presently developing another 20.61 million sq. ft. in various parts of Mumbai and other regions. The company has always adhered to high quality design parameters for its projects and several of them have contributed immensely towards transforming the Mumbai skyline.

Why Oberoi Realty?

The company is known for its insistence on innovation and contemporary architecture in addition to top class project execution and quality construction. The company partners with the best in the country and the world and has always stayed abreast of evolving national and global trends in the industry. The company outsources work to leading global and domestic consultants in architecture, engineering, design and construction to accomplish the scalability required for undertaking mega projects.

The company makes use of the latest technologies for project development and believes in core values like transparency, trust and reliability. The company delivers projects on time and strives to create living spaces that enhance quality of life overall. The company is committed towards offering futuristic and revolutionary offerings which are ahead of their time and benchmarked against global practices and trends. The company aims at offering the perfect solutions to discerning customers and follows top class quality systems and processes. Customer centricity is taken very seriously at the company along with teamwork, innovation, honesty, accountability and its I Connect philosophy where open and transparent communication amongst stakeholders and customers is encouraged.

Major Projects

Introducing Oberoi Maxima, a luxurious residential project located in Andheri East, a prime sublocation in the heart of Mumbai. Strategically situated, this property benefits from its close proximity to several major roads, including Swami Vivekanand Road, JogeshwariVikroli Link Road, and Western Express Highway, providing easy access to various parts of the city. The project is also registered under the Maharashtra Real Estate Regulatory Authority (RERA) with registration number P51800017154.

Oberoi Maxima offers a range of amenities to ensure a comfortable and enjoyable living experience. The project features a well-equipped gymnasium, power backup, 24 x 7 security, and a reading room/library, making it an ideal choice for those who value convenience and luxury. The surrounding environment is also well-maintained, with a normal park/central green area that provides a peaceful retreat from the hustle and bustle of city life.

The apartments at Oberoi Maxima are designed to provide a perfect blend of comfort, style, and functionality. The project offers 3 BHK apartments in various sizes, ranging from 1313 sq. ft. to 1752 sq. ft. The properties are finished with high-quality specifications, including oil-bound distemper walls, Italian/Imported marble flooring in the master bedroom, and more. With its prime location, excellent amenities, and luxurious specifications, Oberoi Maxima is an excellent choice for those looking to invest in a premium residential property in Andheri East.

developer.name: Oberoi Realty
developer.description:
Oberoi Realty is one of the country’s biggest and most reputed developers. The company is always on a quest to ensure vibrant and fulfilling relationships between spaces and their occupants. The company began its journey almost three decades earlier with a view towards redefining housing solutions for customers at par with the best global parameters when the paradigm shift in Mumbai from the southern island towards the suburbs took place.

The portfolio of Oberoi Realty properties encompasses more than 39 projects at strategic locations in Mumbai which cumulatively comprise approximately 9.18 million sq. ft. The company is presently developing another 20.61 million sq. ft. in various parts of Mumbai and other regions. The company has always adhered to high quality design parameters for its projects and several of them have contributed immensely towards transforming the Mumbai skyline.

Why Oberoi Realty?

The company is known for its insistence on innovation and contemporary architecture in addition to top class project execution and quality construction. The company partners with the best in the country and the world and has always stayed abreast of evolving national and global trends in the industry. The company outsources work to leading global and domestic consultants in architecture, engineering, design and construction to accomplish the scalability required for undertaking mega projects.

The company makes use of the latest technologies for project development and believes in core values like transparency, trust and reliability. The company delivers projects on time and strives to create living spaces that enhance quality of life overall. The company is committed towards offering futuristic and revolutionary offerings which are ahead of their time and benchmarked against global practices and trends. The company aims at offering the perfect solutions to discerning customers and follows top class quality systems and processes. Customer centricity is taken very seriously at the company along with teamwork, innovation, honesty, accountability and its I Connect philosophy where open and transparent communication amongst stakeholders and customers is encouraged.

Major Projects

There are several landmark Oberoi Realty projects built over the years and here’s taking a look at some of them:

  • Priviera- This ultra luxurious and landmark project offers boutique privileges and comfort at one of the poshest residential locations in Mumbai. The project has been designed by the renowned Guz Architects form Singapore and the structural design has been taken care of by Meinhardt, an award winning firm from Singapore. The project is located in close proximity to the Arabian Sea and the domestic and international airports. The project comes with a rooftop infinity pool, gorgeous views of the Arabian Sea, a complete floor dedicated to every apartment, multiple parking levels and car lifts, 360 degree air and light ventilation and a show flat designed by Sussanne Khan and her Charcoal Project
  • Prisma- This landmark project offers spacious and beautifully designed 4 BHK apartments with spacious balconies to residents. The project comes with impeccable landscaping and lies along the Jogeshwari-Vikhroli Link Road. The project offers easy access to the Western Express Highway and offers premium amenities and facilities to residents
  • Oberoi Woods- This premium residential project is located at Goregaon East off the Western Express Highway and spreads over 80 acres in all. The project offers nature friendly layouts to residents along with gorgeous views of the Aarey greens. The project is characteristic of exquisite finishing, the very best and innovative construction techniques and contemporary designs and layouts
