developer.name: Tata
developer.description:
Tata Housing Group is one of the country’s biggest and most reputed real estate development companies and is a part of the salt to software Tata conglomerate, one of the country’s oldest and most trusted business houses. Tata Housing Developers was revived in the year 2006 and has since evolved into one of the leading companies in the sector.

The portfolio of Tata Housing properties includes multiple residential, commercial and retail projects and the company aims at offering top notch life spaces to customers through continual innovation. The company is a pioneer with regard to property development by leading corporates in India. The company has huge real estate properties in big metros and mini metros. The company has substantial land banks in Ahmedabad, Bangalore, Mumbai, Chandigarh, Kolkata and Gurgaon and is acquiring more such land parcels.

The company offers properties in almost all consumer segments from value based housing to ultra luxury housing solutions. The products of the company range between INR 5 lakhs and INR 14 crore on an average. The company is currently developing more than 70 million sq. ft. and projects in the pipeline also cumulatively cover another 19 million sq. ft. The company has also developed several path breaking and sustainable townships across the country over the years.

The company has a significant presence in Bhubaneswar, Lonavala, Vadgaon and Goa as it seeks to expand its footprint across tier I and II cities in India. It has also ventured into property development in global markets like Maldives with an eye on Sri Lanka and other South Asian countries for future developments.

Why Tata?

All Tata residential projects are witness to the company’s expertise across key aspects of real estate development including land identification and acquisition, careful project planning, suitable project designing, sales and marketing, project execution and also property services and estate management. The company adheres to stringent quality standards for its projects and believes in total transparency and business ethics. The company also offers maintenance services at its projects that rank up with the best. The company aims at creating homes that are based on a deep understanding of customer needs and preferences.

All Tata Housing projects are built after comprehensive market research which also influences the design and implementation. The company works with globally feted design consultants and architects for its projects and offers low cost housing solutions that are tailored to medium and low income groups. The company pioneered this segment through its Tata Value Homes banner which was launched in the year 2010 and is a fully owned subsidiary owned by it. The company is committed towards developing certified green buildings which save energy and Bangalore’s first LEED Gold Rated green building, namely Xylem, is a major milestone for the company. Almost all of its major projects are platinum or gold rated as per the IGBC’s pre-certification guidelines.

Major Projects

  • Xylem- Bangalore’s 1st LEED Gold Certified project, this awe inspiring edifice is a major landmark for the company
  • Prive- Located at Lonavala, this premium project offers soothing environs, breath taking views and total nature friendliness
  • Amantra- Located at Mumbai, this project offers a fascinating mix of high and mid rise towers that ensures funneling of cool air into each home along with ample natural light

developer.description:
Ekta World Developers was founded in the year 1987. The portfolio of Ekta World properties cumulatively covers more than 14.40 million sq. ft. across 52 strategic and picturesque locations. Ekta World Builders counts more than 14, 255 happy customers as its biggest strength and is committed towards transforming local landscapes with awe inspiring designs and global lifestyles. The company aims at a strategic fusion of grandeur and simplicity for the benefit of customers.

Ekta World Realty has developed several projects in Mumbai and other cities in Maharashtra. The Ekta World Group has always focused on the comfort of residents and believes in crafting long lasting customer relationships. The company has developed several big ticket residential complexes in the western suburbs of Mumbai including Bandra and Dahisar and in Virar, Nashik and Pune. The company has substantial experience in the industry and develops 3-4 lakh sq. ft. every year on an average. The company believes in offering supreme and undiluted luxury to customers at its projects and challenges typical design norms. The company focuses hugely on offering environment friendly housing solutions to customers.

Why Ekta World?

All Ekta World residential projects are environment friendly and green projects. The company believes in transparency, customer commitment and radical and innovative architectural and design layouts. The company focuses on offering high quality projects to customers and adheres to stringent quality and construction standards. The company adheres to guidelines as part of its ISO 9001:2000 certification.

The company believes in fusing simplicity and elegance with innovation and opulence at its projects. The company also offers luxurious interiors to customers along with strategic locations and premium amenities. The company strives to create a community like atmosphere for residents at its projects. The company also aims at offering unmatched customer satisfaction and makes use of the latest technologies and systems for project development.

Major Projects

There are several landmark Ekta World projects that have stood out for their designs and amenities alike. Here’s taking a look at some of them:

  • Ekta Skypolis- One of the biggest and most awe inspiring projects in Mumbai’s upscale Goregaon West suburb, the project is an ode to sheer luxury and affluence. The project offers luxuriously designed housing solutions to residents along with premium amenities and facilities. The project is well linked to several schools, shopping malls, gourmet stores and shopping arcades. The project goes all the way up to 36 storeys
  • Ekta Invictus- This landmark project is located at Dadar East and offers premium 4 BHK apartments to buyers. The project offers an amazing view of the Five Gardens and the finest imported marble. The project has 7 podium car parking levels in addition to delightfully landscaped gardens, well equipped gymnasium and much more. The neo contemporary architectural layout is hard to resist
  • Corner View- This premium project offers well designed 2, 3 and 4 BHK apartments at the prime location of Bandra West in South Mumbai. The project is surrounded by entertainment zones, fine dining restaurants, high street retail outlets, cafes and clubs. The project offers premium amenities and facilities to residents along with elevated and luxurious lifestyles

images.name: Master Plan Image 3
images.description:
Atul Second Avenue is a project designed with functional flow and essential amenities.
Land Use & Density

The master plan primarily illustrates a single commercial or mixed-use building, which incorporates specific facilities such as a bank and a restaurant. The building is surrounded by dedicated areas for surface parking, internal driveways, and landscaped green zones along the property perimeter.

Connectivity & Access
  • The property is directly accessible from an 18.30 MT. WIDE D.P. Road, located along its south-eastern boundary.
  • A main entry point from this road leads to a convenient drop-off point directly fronting the building's entrance.
  • Two separate service entry/exit points are strategically placed on the D.P. Road to manage operational traffic efficiently.
  • An internal driveway system circles the building, providing comprehensive vehicular circulation and access to all parking areas.
On-Site Features & Amenities
  • The building boasts a prominent double-height entrance lobby, creating a grand welcoming space.
  • Dedicated internal spaces are allocated for a bank and a restaurant, catering to essential services and dining needs.
  • Extensive surface parking facilities are distributed around the building for visitor and tenant convenience.
  • Critical infrastructure, including a DG Set and a Substation, is located on the eastern side of the property to ensure continuous power supply.
Key Dimensions & Figures
  • The primary road providing access to the property has a width of 18.30 meters.
  • The master plan includes one main entry point for general access to the property.
  • There are two distinct service entry/exit points visible for logistical operations.

topProjects.seoDescription:
Introducing Atul Second Avenue, a premier commercial project located in the heart of Andheri East. With its strategic positioning along the Jogeshwari-Vikroli Link Road and Western Express Highway, this project offers unparalleled connectivity to major business hubs, amenities, and everyday essentials. The project is registered with the Maharashtra Real Estate Regulatory Authority (RERA) under the registration number P51800052424.

Atul Second Avenue boasts a range of luxurious amenities that cater to the needs of modern professionals. From power backup to 24x7 security, this project prioritizes convenience and safety above all. Additionally, residents can unwind at the in-house cafe or coffee bar, and appreciate the efforts made towards a sustainable future through rainwater harvesting. With a robust RCC frame structure, this project exudes strength and durability.

Choose from our available unit options to suit your business needs. Select from office spaces ranging from 708 Sq. Ft. to 2782 Sq. Ft., with prices starting from 1.80 Cr to 7.09 Cr. With its exceptional location, world-class amenities, and impressive specifications, Atul Second Avenue is the perfect choice for entrepreneurs and professionals looking to establish a strong presence in Andheri East.

locality_summary.headline: Andheri East: Connected, Convenient, Congested Hub
locality_summary.overall_summary: Andheri East is a highly connected and commercially vibrant locality in Mumbai, offering easy access to transportation hubs, employment centers, and social amenities. The area is especially popular among working professionals due to its proximity to SEEPZ, MIDC, and the airport. However, it struggles with traffic congestion, waterlogging during monsoons, and limited green spaces, creating challenges for some residents.
